But BGP can also be hijacked for large-scale spying, data interception, or as a sort of denial of service attack.
If he doesn't know what he's talking about—like an ISP advertising a bad BGP route—you could end up stuck in endless mall traffic.
Is BGP Safe Yet will test your ISP by offering a legitimate route and an invalid one to load two pages.
If your ISP catches the invalid route and only loads the page on the real route, it passes the test.
Even with a large number services still not offering BGP protections, you can still reap benefits from those that do.